# 1. Accessing Systems and Obtaining Support
### Guided Exercise: Configuring SSH Key-based Authentication
- ssh: ssh *user@server*
- change user: su - *user*
- generate ssh keys (with paraphrase): ssh-keygen -f *location*  (optional if default location)
-  Send public key to *user@server*): ssh-copy-id -i *location* (optional if default location) *user@server*
- execute command remotely: ssh -i *location* (optional if default location) operator1@servera *command ex. hostname*
- -f vs -i

### Guided Exercise: Getting Help from Red Hat Customer Portal
- systemctl status/start/stop *system ex. jboss*
